$interpreted: Apothecary: Sir! Sir, can I interest you in this tincture from the Capybara Tribe? Just one bottle and you'll wake up a true master!
Customer: No way, only a sucker would fall for that!
Apothecary: I just can't get rid of any of this Capybara stuff... What'll I do now...
???: Got your loot all ready for me?
Apothecary: K-Kaito, this is all I've got... Please... Give me some more time for the rest...!
Kaito: ...All right, three more days. If I don't get it by then... I'll smash your stall to smithereens!
Apothecary: I'll have it ready!! Thank you for your graciousness!!
Sennosuke: Master, he'll cough it up right now if you sock him one, won't he?
Kaito: True, I'd get even more off him that way, but we've got enough to last us already. No harm in giving him three more days.
Sennosuke: But Master, you've loaned out everything we had left. If we don't get some cash now...
Sennosuke: And if we can't find us a job soon, we'll be totally broke!
Kaito: ...Not to worry, there'll always be someone in need of our services. We'll just have to scrimp a little for now!
Arrogant Hoodlum: Oooh, who do we have here? Well if it isn't the big man himself, Kaito. You're looking right down~ and~ out~
Excited Hoodlum: Yeah, and all that talk about finding a good job's come to nothing. Nobody wants to hire him, so he's back to his old loan-sharking~

Arrogant Hoodlum: How about you pay us a visit at the Secret Society? We'll keep you well fed and clothed~ Nobody'd be stupid enough to turn down some free meals and go on living in hardship, would they?
Sennosuke: Why you little...!
Kaito: Ignore them, Sennosuke.
Arrogant Hoodlum: How about it? Maybe if you get on your knees in front of the boss he'll let you back in again, for old times' sake~
Excited Hoodlum: Cat got your tongue, Kaito? You must be full of regrets now, eh?
Sennosuke: What Master thinks is none of your damned business!
Sennosuke: You scoundrels've got no room to talk neither!
Excited Hoodlum: I'll remember you! Better hope you don't run into the boss again any time soon!
Kaito: Enough, Sennosuke!
Sennosuke: What're you holding me back for!
Kaito: How many times have I told you, you can't go around beating on everyone you meet! Just ignore them. Let's go.
Edensnatch Manager: Come one come all! Once in every twenty years! Registration for the Capybara Tribe's Edensnatch Competition is open now!
Edensnatch Manager: Whether you're a warrior out to make a name for yourself, or a spectator out to see something spectacular, you won't be disappointed!
Sennosuke: Master, what's an Edensnatch?
Kaito: Oh, that... It's a competition organized by the Capybara Tribe. If you can grab hold of the sign, you'll be allowed to participate in the Alliance's Martial Arts Tourney.
Sennosuke: The Marital Arts Tourney!? Are you gonna join the Edensnatch, then, Master?
Kaito: ...I suppose so. It's open to everybody.
Sennosuke: Are you gonna enter your name then, Master? You're so strong, there's no way you won't come first!
Sennosuke: If you win, those rascals'll never come to bother us again!
Kaito: ...All right, I'll give it a go.
Edensnatch Manager: W-what are you doing here?
Kaito: What? Got a problem?
Edensnatch Manager: The Edensnatch isn't for the likes of you...
Sennosuke: What's that supposed to mean...
???: Apologies, please make way.
???: Greetings, I'd like to join the Edensnatch.
Edensnatch Manager: Oh, Yan-Bo, you've finally come.
Sennosuke: Who's that, Master? What're all those people crowding about for?
Kaito: That's Yan-Bo. His martial arts skills are widely renowned. He's been preparing to establish his own school lately.
Doubtful Beast: Hey, don't tell me that punk's gonna join the Edensnatch now, too?
Curious Beast: Looks like it, I just hear him say he wanted to...
Doubtful Beast: What gives? Hoodlums shouldn't be allowed in!
Sennosuke: So what if we're hoodlums? Mind your own business! What's it to do with you lot if we wanna join?!
Kaito: ...Stop, Sennosuke. It won't change anything.
Sennosuke: Master, back me up here!
Kaito: This isn't the first time. Save your breath.
Kaito: Fine, I'm not joining. Let's go, Sennosuke.
Edensnatch Manager: ...Yan-Bo! What are you doing?
Edensnatch Manager: Yan...
Yan-Bo: The rules say it in black and white, the competition's open to anybody. You've no right to turn them away.
Yan-Bo: I admire your courage.
Yan-Bo: Sometimes we need an opportunity to change people's perceptions of us. The Edensnatch would be just such an opportunity for you, don't miss it.
Kaito: Thank you.
Yan-Bo: I look forward to seeing you in the arena. Farewell.
Kaito: I'll join.
Sennosuke: Master, how come you'll join only when Yan-Bo asks you?
Kaito: He's right. This is an opportunity. And... He doesn't seem to carry any prejudices towards us.
Sennosuke: Oh? Do you think you can beat him?
Kaito: I've heard of Yan-Bo's strength, but I'll do my best.
Edensnatch Manager: Yan-Bo, about that tincture I mentioned last time...
Yan-Bo: I'm sorry, I have a disciple waiting on me. I must go.
Yan-Bo: I've been so busy with putting my school together lately, there's just so much to do. I've got to go, but let's talk about it next time!
Edensnatch Manager: (He only cares about opening his school and picking up followers... Looks like... we'll have to take care of this ourselves...)
